parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: and may be accompanied by a loss of power steering and power brakes. The vehicle may jerk back and forth
and the RPMs may drop to zero. In some cases
the vehicle may not start at all or may only start after a few minutes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft sensor can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or hesitates while driving
the vehicle makes a clicking noise when trying to start
the lights flicker or go off and on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TCM can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose control and increase the risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbags to deploy unexpectedly or not deploy in the event of a crash, leading to increased risk of injury or death.
Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
the vehicle jerks or lurches forward
the check engine light or transmission warning light illuminates.
